2Fjapanese-planes-sank-prince-of-wales-repulse-ending-battleship-era-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_top%5C%22%3Ethe%20battleship's%20reign%20came%20to%20an%20end%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20name%20Dreadnought%20is%20still%20a%20defining%20one.%20The%20Royal%20Navy's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.baesystems.com%2Fen%2Fheritage%2Fdreadnought-submarine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20nuclear-powered%20submarine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20service%20from%201963%20to%201980%2C%20was%20also%20called%20HMS%20Dreadnought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20more%20than%20100%20years%20after%20the%20first%20Dreadnought%2C%20another%20is%20in%20the%20works.%20This%20one%2C%20the%20first%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.naval-technology.com%2Fprojects%2Fdreadnought-class-nuclear-powered-ballistic-missile-submarines%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20class%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20nuclear-powered%20ballistic-missile%20submarines%2C%20will%20again%20usher%20in%20a%20new%20era%20of%20warship%20for%20Britain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAt-sea%20deterrent%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22British%20Royal%20Navy%20submarine%20HMS%20Dreadnought%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3b171ec14ba0019f33de1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Royal%20Navy%20submarine%20HMS%20Dreadnought%20in%20April%201963.%3Cp%3ESSPL%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBritain's%20new%20class%20of%20nuclear-powered%20ballistic-missile%20submarines%2C%20designated%20as%20SSBNs%2C%20will%20fill%20a%20looming%20gap%20in%20the%20country's%20nuclear%20deterrent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhereas%20other%20nuclear-armed%20countries%20employ%20a%20triad%20of%20delivery%20systems%20%E2%80%94%20ground-launched%2C%20air-launched%2C%20and%20sea-launched%20%E2%80%94%20to%20ensure%20their%20nuclear%20capability%20will%20survive%20an%20attack%20and%20thus%20guarantee%20a%20credible%20nuclear%20deterrent%2C%20Britain%20has%20relied%20solely%20on%20submarine-launched%20ballistic%20missiles%20since%201998%2C%20when%20it%20retired%20its%20air-dropped%20nuclear%20gravity%20bombs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Royal%20Navy%20has%20had%20at%20least%20one%20SSBN%20on%20patrol%20as%20part%20of%20Operation%20Relentless%2C%20Britain's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.royalnavy.mod.uk%2Fnews-and-latest-activity%2Foperations%2Fglobal%2Fcontinuous-at-sea-deterrent%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtinuous%20at%20sea%20deterrent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20since%201969%2C%20making%20it%20the%20country's%20longest%20ongoing%20military%20operation.%20The%20current%20British%20SSBN%20force%20is%20made%20up%20of%20four%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.royalnavy.mod.uk%2Fthe-equipment%2Fsubmarines%2Fballistic-submarines%2Fvanguard-class%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVanguard-class%3C%2Fa%3E%20subs%2C%20which%20were%20built%20between%201986%20and%201998.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strain%20of%20decades%20of%20near-constant%20deployments%20has%20taken%20a%20toll%20on%20the%20Vanguards.%20Originally%20meant%20to%20serve%20for%2025%20years%2C%20the%20subs%20have%20had%20their%20service%20lives%20extended%20three%20times.%20Their%20overall%20lifespan%20is%20now%20expected%20to%20be%2037%20to%2038%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vanguard-class%20submarine%20HMS%20Victorious%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3b6f8ec14ba0019f347b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221206%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVanguard-class%20submarine%20HMS%20Victorious%20near%20Faslane%20in%20April%202013.%3Cp%3EUK%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202007%2C%20the%20British%20Parliament%20approved%20a%20plan%20for%20four%20new%20SSBNs%20to%20replace%20the%20Vanguards.%20After%20years%20of%20design%20work%2C%20construction%20on%20the%20first%20boat%2C%20HMS%20Dreadnought%2C%20began%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20ensure%20successful%20and%20efficient%20construction%20and%20delivery%20of%20the%20new%20class%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20created%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Forganisations%2Fsubmarine-delivery-agency%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESubmarine%20Delivery%20Agency%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202017%20to%20serve%20as%20an%20executive%20agency%20responsible%20for%20procurement%2C%20in-service%20support%2C%20and%20decommissioning%20of%20all%20Royal%20Navy%20nuclear%20submarines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20later%2C%20the%20two%20companies%20contracted%20to%20build%20the%20Dreadnought%2C%20BAE%20Systems%20and%20Rolls%20Royce%2C%20formed%20the%20%26quot%3BDreadnought%20Alliance%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20commercial%20arrangement%20that%20ensures%20constant%20communication%20and%20collaboration%20between%20the%20companies%2C%20including%20on%20things%20like%20a%20common%20cost%20model%2C%20mutually%20agreed%20scheduling%20and%20breakdown%20of%20work%2C%20and%20reporting%20procedures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20Dreadnought%20class%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22931%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22British%20Royal%20Navy%20ballistic-missile%20submarine%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3b6f7ec14ba0019f347ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22638%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20rendering%20from%202016%20of%20the%20ballistic-missile%20sub%20meant%20to%20replace%20the%20Vanguard%20class.%3Cp%3EBritish%20Royal%20Navy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20about%20500%20feet%20long%20and%20with%20a%20displacement%20of%2017%2C200%20tons%2C%20the%20Dreadnoughts%20will%20be%20the%20largest%20submarines%20ever%20built%20by%20the%20UK.%20Each%20boat%20will%20have%20a%20lifespan%20of%20at%20least