Navy's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnavy-may-keep-ohio-missile-subs-longer-over-columbia-cost-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EColumbia-class%20boats%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20have%20four.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20the%20CMC%20project%2C%20the%20UK%20is%20also%20involved%20in%20the%20US%20Navy's%20Trident%20II%20D5%20service-life%20extension%20program%2C%20which%20aims%20to%20stretch%20the%20missile's%20service%20life%20as%20far%20as%20the%20early%202060s.%20The%20British%20government%20previously%20indicated%20that%20its%20Tridents%20will%20need%20to%20be%20replaced%20in%20the%202040s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20future%20fleet%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Royal%20Navy%20submarine%20HMS%20Astute%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3b6f8ec14ba0019f347ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERoyal%20Navy%20attack%20sub%20HMS%20Astute%20after%20its%20launch%20at%20a%20shipyard%20in%20Barrow-in-Furness%20in%20June%202007.%3Cp%3EChristopher%20Furlong%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20Dreadnought-class%20subs%20will%20be%20built%3A%20Dreadnought%2C%20Valiant%2C%20Warspite%2C%20and%20King%20George%20VI.%20Construction%20of%20Valiant%20started%20in%202019%20and%20work%20on%20Warspite%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.royalnavy.mod.uk%2Fnews-and-latest-activity%2Fnews%2F2023%2Ffebruary%2F09%2F20230209-work-starts-on-third-new-nuclear-deterrence-submarine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebegan%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202022%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20announced%20that%20Dreadnought%20had%20entered%20Delivery%20Phase%203%2C%20during%20which%20the%20sub%20will%20eventually%20leave%20the%20BAE%20shipyard%20in%20Barrow-in-Furness%20for%20sea%20trials%2C%20yielding%20lessons%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fresearchbriefings.files.parliament.uk%2Fdocuments%2FCBP-8010%2FCBP-8010.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewill%20be%20applied%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20construction%20of%20other%20Dreadnought-class%20subs.%20The%20Royal%20Navy%20plans%20to%20commission%20HMS%20Dreadnought%20sometime%20in%20the%20early%202030s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20being%20the%20largest%20British%20subs%20ever%2C%20the%20Dreadnought%20class%20will%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20expensive%20defense%20projects%20in%20British%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuilding%20the%20four%20subs%20is%20expected%20to%20cost%20a%20little%20over%20%2439.5%20billion%2C%20a%20total%20that%20includes%20inflation%20over%20the%2035-year%20life%20of%20the%20program.%20The%20British%20government%20has%20also%20set%20up%20a%20contingency%20fund%20of%20about%20%2412.75%20billion%2C%20money%20that%20can%20be%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fresearchbriefings.files.parliament.uk%2Fdocuments%2FCBP-8010%2FCBP-8010.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ere-profiled%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20to%20keep%20the%20program%20on%20track.%20The%20MoD%20has%20already%20accessed%20about%2020%25%20of%20the%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20British%20lawmakers%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommittees.parliament.uk%2Fpublications%2F22125%2Fdocuments%2F164255%2Fdefault%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpressed%20concern%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20would%20view%20the%20contingency%20fund%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20blank%20cheque%2C%20freeing%20it%20from%20the%20need%20to%20control%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ministry%20said%20in%20its%202022%20update%20to%20Parliament%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fpublications%2Fthe-united-kingdoms-future-nuclear-deterrent-the-2022-update-to-parliament%2Fthe-united-kingdoms-f