1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20grew%20my%20business%20from%204%20people%20to%2016%2C000%20in%207%20years.%20Here%20are%205%20ways%20I've%20seen%20new%20business%20owners%20fail%20when%20they%20expand%2C%20and%20how%20I've%20avoided%20making%20those%20mistakes.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sudhir%20Agarwal%20speaks%20at%20the%20opening%20of%20Everise's%20premises%20in%20Colombia.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64abb3558ed31300199e3d72%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESudhir%20Agarwal%20started%20his%20own%20firm%20in%202016%20and%20started%20off%20by%20acquiring%20a%20loss-making%20company.%20Over%20the%20next%207%20years%2C%20he%20grew%20its%20headcount%20to%2016%2C000%20people.%3Cp%3EEverise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESudhir%20Agarwal%20founded%20Everise%20in%202016%20with%20a%20team%20of%20four%20employees%20in%20Singapore.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20his%20company%20employs%20more%20than%2016%2C000%20people%20in%20eight%20countries.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHe%20outlined%20five%20common%20mistakes%20small-business%20owners%20make%20as%20they%20try%20to%20expand.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20an%20interview%20with%20Sudhir%20Agarwal%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Everise%2C%20which%20runs%20outsourced%20customer%20service%20for%20other%20firms.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20I%20left%20my%20job%20as%20the%20CEO%20of%20an%20IT%20consultancy%20to%20start%20my%20own%20firm%20%E2%80%94%20Everise.%20We%20were%20a%20small%20team%20at%20the%20time%2C%20with%20just%20four%20people%20in%20Singapore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20goal%20was%20to%20disrupt%20what%20was%20and%20still%20is%20a%20very%20traditional%20customer%20service%20industry%20by%20investing%20in%20technology%20and%20new%20talent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20by%20acquiring%20an%20outsourcing%20company%20that%20was%20losing%20money%2C%20and%20had%20around%207%2C000%20employees%20in%202017.%20We%20managed%20to%20stabilize%20in%20two%20years%2C%20and%20in%202020%2C%20Brookfield%20bought%20a%20majority%20stake%20in%20our%20company%20at%20a%20valuation%20of%20%24500%20million.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20was%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20that%20we%20really%20saw%20a%20pivot%20in%20growth.%20We%20shifted%2095%25%20of%20our%20employees%20to%20remote%20work%20within%20weeks.%20Everise%20now%20employs%2016%2C000%20people%20in%20eight%20countries%2C%20and%20our%20headquarters%20are%20in%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20five%20common%20mistakes%20I%20see%20new%20business%20owners%20make%20when%20they%20try%20to%20expand%20their%20companies%2C%20and%20what%20I%20do%20to%20address%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Not%20paying%20close%20enough%20attention%20to%20the%20quality%20of%20people%20you%20hire%20when%20scaling%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20startups%20and%20small%20businesses%20are%20in%20their%20early%20stages%2C%20manpower%20becomes%20a%20pressing%20need.%20Many%20business%20owners%20start%20hiring%20rapidly%20so%20they%20can%20meet%20demands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20common%20mistake%20that%20can%20lead%20to%20more%20cost%20for%20the%20business%20in%20the%20long%20term.%20Hires%20who%20are%20poor%20cultural%20fits%20or%20simply%20cannot%20perform%20their%20roles%20cost%20the%20team%20more%20in%20terms%20of%20morale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20kept%20my%20focus%20on%20building%20a%20No.%201%20team.%20I've%20been%20in%20the%20outsourcing%20business%20for%2025%20years.%20I%20leveraged%20that%20experience%20when%20I%20started%20Everise%2C%20making%20calls%20to%20leaders%20in%20the%20industry%20and%20hoping%20some%20would%20leave%20their%20jobs%20to%20join%20me%20in%20my%20vision.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20person%20who%20joined%20me%20is%20our%20current%20chief%20people%20officer%2C%20who's%20been%20working%20with%20me%20for%2015%20years.%20Today%2C%20we%20have%20a%20below-average%20attrition%20rate%20among%20our%2016%2C000%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20%3Cstrong%3ENot%20putting%20employees%20first%2C%20in%20favor%20of%20prioritizing%20customers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20business%20owner%20aims%20to%20do%20this%20from%20the%20outset%2C%20but%20the%20pressures%20of%20owning%20a%20small%20business%20can%20distract%20from%20what's%20most%20important%20%E2%80%94%20your%20people.%20When%20I%20started%20Everise%2C%20one%20thing%20I%20was%20very%20clear%20on%20was%20that%C2%A0we%20will%20never%20miss%20a%20paycheck%20for%20any%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20really%20proud%20we%20were%20able%20to%20achieve%20this%2C%20though%20it%20certainly%20wasn't%20easy.%20The%20business%20we%20acquired%20that%20would%20become%20Everise%20was%20at%20the%20time%20loss-making.%20It%20took%2024%20months%20for%20us%20to%20stabilize.%20So%20there%20were%20months%20where%20I%20had%20to%20dip%20into%20my%20own%20pocket%20to%20ensure%20staff%20were%20paid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Building%20too%20many%20layers%20between%20top%20managers%20and%20employees%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECommunication%20shouldn't%20always%20be%20top%20down.%20The%20most%20valuable%20feedback%20comes%20from%20your%20frontliners%2C%20those%20who%20are%20on%20the%20ground%20with%20customers%20on%20a%20daily%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20reasons%20I%20started%20Everise%20was%20that%20I%20was%20tired%20of%20dealing%20with%20needless%20bureaucracy.%20Here%2C%20everyone%20has%20a%20direct%20line%20to%20me.%20If%20there%20are%20any%20signs%20of%20blocks%20emerging%20anywhere%2C%20we%20kill%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20foundations%20were%20set%20in%20place%20very%20early%20and%20remain%20core%20pillars%20today.%20Happy%20employees%20equate%20to%20happy%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Micro%20managing%3A%20It%20takes%20a%20team%2C%20not%20a%20one-man%20show%2C%20to%20sustain%20a%20successful%20company%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMicro%20management%20is%20never%20sustainable.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20this%20the%20hard%20way%20in%202018.%20It%20was%20easy%20to%20micro%20manage%20a%20small%20business%2C%20but%20as%20we%20grew%20and%20made%20some%20acquisitions%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20that%20wasn't%20going%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuccessful%20entrepreneurs%20and%20businesses%20are%20where%20they%20are%20because%20of%20the%20teams%20that%20support%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mantra%20has%20always%20been%20to%20hire%20people%20who%20are%20smarter%20than%20me%20so%20I%20can%20learn%20from%20them%2C%20especially%20when%20hiring%20leaders%20in%20your%20organization.%20When%20you%20have%20strong%20leaders%2C%20good%20talent%20will%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Not%20'partying'%20as%20hard%20as%20they%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20bit%20tongue%20in%20cheek%2C%20but%20leaders%20have%20to%20invest%20the%20time%20in%20getting%20to%20know%20their%20people%20socially.%20Not%20everything%20is%20about%20business.%20Enjoy%20the%20process%2C%20and%20grow%20your%20network%20of%20connections%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20organize%20after-work%20dinner%20and%20drinks%20with%20employees%20and%20business%20associates%2C%20so%20they%20can%20get%20to%20know%20each%20other%20outside%20of%20business%20settings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freasons-new-business-owners-fail-entrepreneur-everise-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691926021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c8b907048ff200190e97db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freasons-new-business-owners-fail-entrepreneur-everise-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Agarwal%20manages%2016%2C000%20employees%20in%20eight%20countries%2C%20after%20leaving%20his%20job%20as%20the%20CEO%20of%20an%20IT%20consultancy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40insider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freasons-new-business-owners-fail-entrepreneur-everise-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2218%20Deaths%20In%2024%20Hours%20In%20Maharashtra%20Hospital%2C%20Probe%20Panel%20Formed%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EEighteen%20patients%20have%20died%20in%20the%20last%2024%20hours%20at%20the%20Chhatrapati%20Shivaji%20Maharaj%20Hospital%20in%20Kalwa%20in%20Thane%2C%20civic%20commissioner%20Abhijit%20Bangar%20said%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20comprise%2010%20women%20and%20eight%20men%2C%20of%20which%20six%20are%20from%20Thane%20city%2C%20four%20from%20Kalyan%2C%20three%20from%20Sahapur%2C%20one%20each%20from%20Bhiwandi%2C%20Ulhasnagar%20and%20Govandi%20(in%20Mumbai)%2C%20one%20patient%20is%20from%20some%20other%20place%20and%20and%20one%20is%20unidentified%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwelve%20of%20the%20dead%20were%20above%20the%20age%20of%2050%2C%20Mr%20Bangar%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20state%20health%20minister%20Tanaji%20Sawant%20and%20local%20Deputy%20Commissioner%20of%20Police%20Ganesh%20Gawde%20had%20put%20the%20number%20of%20deaths%20at%2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20a%20news%20conference%2C%20Mr%20Bangar%20said%20Chief%20Minister%20Eknath%20Shinde%20had%20taken%20feedback%20about%20the%20situation%20and%20had%20ordered%20the%20setting%20up%20of%20an%20independent%20probe%20committee%20that%20will%20be%20headed%20by%20the%20commissioner%20of%20health%20services%20and%20will%20include%20collector%2C%20civic%20chief%2C%20director%20of%20health%20services%2C%20interventionist%20at%20state-run%20JJ%20Hospital%20in%20Mumbai%20and%20civic%20surgeon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20will%20carry%20out%20probe%20into%20the%20clinical%20aspect%20of%20the%20deaths%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20patients%20had%20complications%20of%20kidney%20stone%2C%20chronic%20paralysis%2C%20ulcer%2C%20pneumonia%2C%20kerosene%20poisoning%2C%20septicemia%20etc%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20line%20of%20treatment%20will%20be%20probed%20and%20statements%20of%20kin%20of%20the%20deceased%20etc%20will%20be%20recorded.%20Allegations%20of%20negligence%20levelled%20by%20some%20kin%20is%20a%20serious%20matter%2C%20which%20the%20probe%20committee%20will%20look%20into%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Bangar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20entire%20COVID%20staff%20of%20500%20has%20been%20shifted%20to%20this%20hospital%20and%20additional%20nursing%20staff%20has%20been%20appointed.%20We%20are%20also%20aiming%20to%20have%20round%20the%20clock%20post%20mortem%20facility%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20in%20the%20day%2C%20state%20health%20minister%20Tanaji%20Sawant%20said%20the%20dean%20of%20the%20hospital%20had%20been%20asked%20to%20submit%20a%20report%20in%20two%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Thane%20Municipal%20Corporation%20official%20said%20the%20deaths%20were%20being%20analysed%20and%20several%20civic%20officials%20are%20at%20the%20heavily-patronised%20facility%20for%20inspection%20of%20records%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20PTI%2C%20Deputy%20Commissioner%20of%20Police%20Ganesh%20Gawde%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20information%20of%2017%20deaths%20in%20the%20last%2024%20hours.%20We%20have%20been%20told%20the%20usual%20figure%20per%20day%20is%20six%20to%20seven.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BThe%20hospital%20management%20told%20us%20some%20of%20the%20patients%20arrived%20there%20in%20a%20critical%20stage%20and%20succumbed%20during%20treatment.%20Some%20were%20elderly.%20We%20have%20increased%20police%20presence%20at%20the%20hospital%20to%20avoid%20any%20untoward%20incident%20due%20to%20these%20high%20number%20of%20deaths%2C%26quot%3