nt%20out%20their%20houses%20to%20companies%20that%20want%C2%A0coworking%20spaces.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Portland%2C%20Oregon%2C%20startup%20tends%20to%20operate%20in%20suburban%20areas%20to%20be%20close%20to%20where%20workers%20live.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERadious'%20listings%20range%20from%20your%20average%20home%20to%20an%20Airstream%20and%20even%20a%20yurt.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELaundry%20was%20what%20tripped%20up%20Amina%20Moreau's%20plan%20to%20go%20back%20to%20renting%20out%20a%20small%20apartment%20on%20the%20lower%20level%20of%20her%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20late%20summer%202020%20and%20Moreau%20missed%20the%20income%20she%20and%20her%20partner%20had%20been%20able%20to%20draw%20from%20listing%20the%20unit%20on%20Airbnb%20before%20pandemic%20lockdowns%20made%20that%20unworkable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoreau%20was%20eager%20to%20start%20listing%20again%2C%20but%20having%20to%20wash%20strangers'%20sheets%20and%20towels%20at%20a%20time%20when%20many%20of%20us%20were%20still%20wiping%20down%20our%20groceries%20wouldn't%20fly.%20What%20she%20needed%2C%20in%20essence%2C%20was%20the%20perfect%20house%20guest%3A%20someone%20who%20wouldn't%20stay%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20breakfast%20one%20Saturday%2C%20Moreau%20and%20her%20partner%20landed%20on%20the%20idea%20of%20making%20the%20space%20available%20to%20people%20who%20just%20wanted%20a%20place%20to%20work%20for%20the%20day.%20So%20they%20beefed%20up%20their%20WiFi%2C%20bought%20a%20desk%2C%20and%20started%20offering%20the%20apartment%20as%20a%20freebie%20to%20neighbors%20who%20were%20delighted%20by%20the%20idea%20of%20getting%20to%20look%20at%20someone%20else's%20walls%20for%20a%20few%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemand%20for%20the%20apartment%20getaway%20led%20Moreau%2C%20along%20with%20two%20friends%2C%20to%20start%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fradious.pro%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERadious%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Portland%2C%20Oregon%2C%20company%20lets%20homeowners%20rent%20to%20companies%20in%20need%20of%20coworking%20spaces.%20Radious%20began%20testing%20its%20app%20in%202021%20and%2C%20by%20early%202022%2C%20the%20company%20was%20up%20and%20running.%20Robin%20Daniels%2C%20the%20former%20CMO%20of%20WeWork%2C%20recently%20decided%20to%20invest%20in%20the%20company%2C%20Moreau%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERadious%20lists%20rentals%20%E2%80%94%20everything%20from%20your%20typical%20house%20to%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fradious.pro%2Flisting-details-guest%2Flfecmprrcefyvmwtvd%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshiny%20trailer%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fradious.pro%2Flisting-details-guest%2Fomoybcqngkhbvulupf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslick%20auditorium%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20in%20Portland%20and%20Milwaukee%C2%A0and%20the%20suburbs%20of%20both.%C2%A0It%20plans%20to%20add%20an%20undisclosed%C2%A0city%20soon%2C%20Moreau%20said.%C2%A0Radious%20also%20lets%C2%A0companies%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhello.radious.pro%2Fsecret-spaces%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erequest%20access%20to%20spaces%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20other%20cities%20across%20the%C2%A0US%20to%C2%A0tap%20into%20a%20network%20of%20not-yet-public%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20listings%20include%20one%20outside%20Milwaukee%20for%20%24114%20a%20day.%20It%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fradious.pro%2Flisting-details-guest%2Fzkqoqywsmijfqounqf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eprivate%20office%20for%20two%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20whiteboard%20and%20refreshments.%20And%20it's%20a%20five-minute%20walk%20to%20Lake%20Michigan%20%E2%80%94%20the%20perfect%20antidote%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.henryford.com%2Fblog%2F2022%2F04%2Ffeeling-drowsy-how-to-overcome-the-midday-slump%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAccording%2520to%2520the%2520Sleep%2520Foundation%2Cthe%2520body%2527s%2520natural%2520circadian%2520rhythm.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20afternoon%20slump%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Another%20listing%20near%20Portland%20is%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fradious.pro%2Flisting-details-guest%2Fzlcrvetgfvdjkthywo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehigh-end%20cabin%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20set%20amid%2015%20acres%20of%20forest.%20That%20one%20goes%20for%20%24496%2C%20including%20fees%2C%20for%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoreau%20told%20Insider%20the%20draw%20for%20workers%20is%20about%20a%20change%20of%20scenery%20and%20about%20escaping%20the%20diversions%20of%20home%20life.%20She%20said%20leaving%20the%20house%20but%20not%20going%20to%20the%20office%20can%20help%20combat%20what%20she%20sees%20as%20the%20three%20downsides%20of%20working%20from%20home%3A%20distractions%2C%20feelings%20of%20isolation%2C%20and%20burnout%20as%20a%20result%20of%20living%20where%20you%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20shut%20off%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20these%20are%20usually%20things%20that%20tend%20to%20creep%20up%20on%20you%20over%20time.%20Working%20from%20home%20for%20a%20month%20or%20two%2C%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20feel%20burnout%20necessarily.%20But%20three%20years%20in%2C%20it%20might%20creep%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20recently%20spoke%20with%20Moreau%20about%20what%20it%20took%20to%20get%20Radious%20running%20and%20what%20the%20company%20looks%20for%20in%20a%20city%20where%20it%20hopes%20to%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20interview%20was%20condensed%20and%20edited%20for%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETell%20me%20a%20little%20bit%20about%20the%20company%20and%20how%20you%20got%20started.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20I%20say%20it's%20like%20Airbnb%20and%20WeWork%20had%20a%20baby.%20But%20effectively%2C%20you%20know%2C%20it's%20a%20B2B%20platform%20that%20outfits%20Airbnbs%20and%20other%20residential%20properties%20with%20workplace%20amenities%2C%20effectively%20turning%20homes%20into%20collaborative%20workspaces%20that%20companies%20rent%20by%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20the%20premise%20behind%20it%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20future-of-work%20conversation%20is%20shifting%20quickly%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20right%20now%2C%20for%20so%20many%20companies%2C%20what's%20top%20of%20mind%20is%20cost%20savings.%20And%20our%20thesis%20is%20that%20it%20really%20doesn't%20make%20sense%20to%20pay%20for%20an%20office%20lease%20seven%20days%20a%20week%20if%20your%20people%20are%20only%20using%20it%20once%20or%20twice.%20The%20economics%20simply%20don't%20add%20up.%20And%20at%20some%20point%2C%20all%20of%20these%20leases%20are%20going%20to%20be%20coming%20up%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20them%20already%20have%20%E2%80%94%20and%20companies%20have%20either%20downsized%20or%20have%20eliminated%20their%20space%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20working%20from%20home%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20eternity%20is%20probably%20not%20the%20be-all%2C%20end-all%20for%20everybody.%20And%20there%20is%20something%20to%20be%20said%20for%20the%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20years%20that%2C%20as%20a%20species%2C%20we've%20gotten%20together%20in%20person.%20People%20need%20a%20place%20to%20go%20to%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0whether%20to%20see%20colleagues%20or%20to%20just%20get%20some%20work-life%20separation.%20And%20that's%20why%20Radious%20exists.%20It's%20on%20a%20fractional%20model.%20It%20saves%20companies%20a%20ton%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20most%20critically%2C%20the%20reason%20why%20we're%20focused%20on%20converting%20effectively%20residential%20properties%20into%20workspaces%20is%20because%20residential%20properties%20tend%20to%20be%20in%20residential%20areas.%20That's%20where%20people%20live.%20And%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20stats%2C%20the%20biggest%20barrier%20to%20returning%20to%20the%20office%20is%20the%20commute.%20And%20so%20we're%20bringing%20the%20office%20to%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20you%20come%20up%20with%20this%20idea%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20August%202020%20and%20our%20Airbnb%20unit%20had%20been%20shut%20down%20for%20a%20few%20months%20at%20that%20point%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20We%20live%20in%20a%20house%20that%20has%20a%20separate%20studio%20apartment%20in%20the%20lower%20level%20that%20we%20had%20been%20Airbnbing.%20It%20covers%20a%20good%20two-thirds%20of%20our%20mortgage%20every%20month%2C%20which%20is%20great%3B%20helps%20with%20housing%20affordability%2C%20etc.%20Problem%20is%2C%20the%20pandemic%20came%20along.%20We%20had%20to%20shut%20everything%20down.%20And%20in%20August%20we%20were%20allowed%20to%20reopen.%20But%20the%20one%20thing%20holding%20us%20back%20was%20laundry.%20It%20was%20the%20idea%20of%20washing%20strangers'%20linens%20during%20a%20pandemic.%20No%2C%20thank%20you.%20But%20we%20couldn't%20keep%20it%20shut%20indefinitely%20so%20we%20started%20brainstorming.%20Can%20we%20get%20creative%3F%20Well%2C%20to%20eliminate%20laundry%2C%20you'd%20have%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20the%20overnight%20component.%20And%20there%20really%20aren't%20any%20platforms%20out%20there%20that%20cater%20to%20day-only%20use%20in%20this%20fashion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20it%20occurred%20to%20us%20that%20at%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20because%20we're%20still%20technically%20in%20lockdowns%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0all%20of%20our%20neighbors%20are%20stuck%20at%20home.%20Their%20kids%20are%20home%20from%20school.%20Dogs%20are%20barking.%20Kids%20are%20screaming.%20How%20does%20a%20working%20parent%20get%20anything%20done%3F%20We%20thought%2C%20what%20if%20we%20buy%20a%20sit-stand%20desk%2C%20upgrade%20the%20WiFi%2C%20and%20invite%20our%20neighbors%20to%20come%20for%20a%20solo%20escape%3F%20Since%2C%20at%20the%20time%2C%20it%20was%20still%20much%20safer%20to%20be%20on%20your%20own.%20And%20we%20tested%20it%20and%20it%20went%20gangbusters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20headshot%20of%20Amina%20Moreau%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d66b20f3f87e001951e0f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmina%20Moreau%3Cp%3ERadious%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20started%20renting%20broadly%20to%20people%20in%20Portland%20in%20January%202022%20and%20then%20a%20bit%20more%20than%20six%20months%20later%2C%20you%20opened%20in%20Milwaukee.%20That%20seems%20fast.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20weren't%20expecting%20to%20expand%20to%20a%20second%20city%20so%20soon%2C%20but%20we%20were%20seeing%20such%20great%20interest%20and%20results%20in%20Portland.%20And%20we%20do%20eventually%20want%20to%20be%20across%20the%20globe.%20And%20so%20we%20started%20feeling%20like%2C%20OK%2C%20we've%20learned%20some%20really%20valuable%20lessons%20here%20in%20Portland%2C%20let's%20start%20learning%20lessons%20about%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20expand%20to%20a%20new%20city.%20Because%20it's%20different%20launching%20into%20a%20second%20city%20than%20it%20is%20starting%20from%20scratch%20in%20a%20first.%20And%20so%20we%20ended%20up%20accelerating%20our%20timeline%20because%20the%20response%20was%20so%20great.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'm%20curious%20about%20what%20made%20Milwaukee%20an%20ideal%20second%20city%20for%20you.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20eight%20or%20nine%20characteristics%20that%20we%20look%20for%20in%20a%20city.%20One%20of%20them%20is%20how%20community-oriented%20is%20it.%20Milwaukee%20and%20Portland%20are%20both%20midsize%20cities.%20And%20Milwaukee%20really%20prides%20itself%20on%20being%20welcoming%20and%20friendly.%20And%20if%20you%20think%20about%20it%2C%20our%20platform%20is%20rooted%20deeply%20in%20community.%20We're%20about%20neighbors%20booking%20neighbors'%20homes%20for%20work.%20And%20so%20you%20want%20to%20be%20launching%20in%20a%20culture%20where%20it's%20second%20nature%20to%20be%20welcoming.%20So%20that's%20one%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20we%20did%20all%20of%20the%20standard%20business%20assessments%20%E2%80%94%20competitive%20landscape%2C%20where%20are%20there%20potential%20customers%2C%20where%20do%20we%20have%20letters%20of%20intent%20from%20employers%20that%20would%20be%20interested%20in%20subscribing%20to%20the%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Milwaukee%20is%20a%20great%20city%20and%20midsized%20cities%20have%20less%20of%20a%20coworking%20presence.%20Other%20coworking%20companies%20focus%20less%20on%20smaller%20cities%20and%20also%20less%20on%20suburbs.%20And%20we%20are%20focused%20on%20the%20suburban%2C%20more-residential%20areas%20where%20people%20are%20typically%20underserved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221323%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20sample%20Radious%20listing%20of%20a%20workspace%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d836d31f51cc00196869cb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20sample%20Radious%20listing%3Cp%3ERadious%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHave%20you%20found%20there's%20a%20benefit%20to%20marketing%20the%20suburban%20angle%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20one%20of%20our%20three%20strongest%20value%20propositions.%20So%20the%20three%20are%20massive%20cost%20savings%20%E2%80%94%20we%20are%20a%20fractional%20model%3B%20you%20pay%20as%20you%20go.%20So%20with%20Radious%20you%20never%20pay%20for%20unused%20real%20estate%20ever%20again.%20The%20second%20value%20prop%20is%20the%20uniqueness%20of%20the%20experience%20because%20now%20instead%20of%20meeting%20at%20a%20typical%20corporate%20office%2C%20you%20have%20access%20to%20a%20network%20of%20spaces.%20Each%20one%20is%20different%20%E2%80%94%20everything%20from%20tiny%20homes%20to%20mansions%2C%201970s%20Airstreams.%20Yurts.%20We%20have%20very%20eclectic%20spaces.%20New%20construction.%20We%20have%20some%20corporate-feeling%20spaces%2C%20some%20very%20homey-feeling%20spaces.%20Variety%20is%20the%20spice%20of%20life.%20And%20then%20the%20third%20value%20prop%20%E2%80%94%20in%20no%20particular%20order%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0is%20the%20proximity%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeyond%20the%20quality%20of%20life%20aspect%20%E2%80%94%20in%20terms%20of%20reducing%20the%20commute%20%E2%80%94%20have%20you%20heard%20any%20clients%20say%20they're%20pleased%20from%20a%20carbon-footprint%20standpoint%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes.%20So%20the%20most%20frequent%20comment%20that%20we%20get%20is%20that%20in%20addition%20to%20helping%20them%20meet%20ESG%20goals%2C%20it's%20also%20a%20really%20great%20way%20to%20engage%20their%20employees.%20Because%20right%20now%2C%20as%20companies%20bring%20people%20together%2C%20the%20number%20one%20priority%20is%20to%20create%20an%20inspiring%20experience.%20And%20it's%20easier%20to%20do%20that%20if%20the%20space%20is%2C%20A%2C%20easy%20to%20get%20to%2C%20B%2C%20really%20cool.%20So%20much%20so%20that%20the%20moment%20you%20walk%20in%20there%2C%20you%20want%20to%20take%20a%20selfie%20and%20post%20it%20to%20Instagram%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%20is%20in%20a%20cool%20neighborhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20maybe%20after%20your%20workday%20or%20your%20meeting%2C%20you%20go%20out%20to%20a%20local%20pub%20and%20do%20a%20team%20happy%20hour.%20And%20the%20beauty%20of%20this%20model%20is%20because%20we're%20all%20over%20the%20region%2C%20you%20can%20go%20to%20a%20different%20neighborhood%20every%20time%20or%20you%20could%20just%20find%20a%20favorite%20and%20go%20there%20each%20time.%20But%20either%20way%2C%20there%20is%20an%20element%20of%20exploration%2C%20not%20just%20of%20each%20property%2C%20but%20of%20different%20neighborhoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20imagine%20a%20neighborhood%20would%20have%20to%20have%20a%20certain%20cool%20factor.%C2%A0%20It%20would%20seem%20like%20some%20suburbs%20that%20are%20just%20house%20after%20house%20may%20not%20be%20as%20attractive.%20Or%20do%20those%20potentially%20even%20have%20their%20own%20value%20if%20you%20really%20just%20need%20the%20space%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20yes%2C%20that's%20exactly%20it%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0going%20back%20to%20my%20previous%20comment%20that%20variety%20is%20the%20name%20of%20the%20game%20here.%20We've%20gotten%20requests%20from%20companies%20also%20for%20the%20farthest-possible%20space.%20They%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20do%20you%20have%20that's%20in%20the%20forest%3F%20Because%20we%20want%20to%20get%20out%20of%20town.%20We%20want%20to%20do%20the%20opposite%20%E2%80%94%20and%20have%20a%20retreat%20where%20it's%20not%20overnight%20because%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20impose%20too%20much.%20But%20let's%20do%20a%20day%20trip%2C%20go%20and%20do%20some%20team-building%20exercises%2C%20have%20a%20working%20lunch%20and%20get%20some%20fresh%20air%20together.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20must%20be%20quite%20a%20job%20to%20vet%20the%20properties%20and%20the%20property%20owners.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20a%20small%20but%20mighty%20host-success%20team%20that%20is%20responsible%20for%20exactly%20that%20%E2%80%94%20and%20really%20building%20relationships%20with%20each%20one%20of%20our%20hosts.%20And%20doing%20things%20like%20virtual%20tours%2C%20sometimes%20in-person%20tours%2C%20and%20making%20sure%20that%20everybody%20is%20set%20up%20for%20success%20and%20making%20sure%20that%20the%20listing%20is%20truly%20representative%20of%20the%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fradious-coworking-spaces-rent-homes-startup-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691922601000%2C%