ey%20suggests.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225497%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d6313d005c4a00183deedc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224123%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy.%3Cp%3EEfrem%20Lukatsky%2FAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20a%20poll%2C%2077.6%25%20of%20Ukrainians%20said%20Zelenskyy%20was%20responsible%20for%20government%20corruption.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20survey%20included%202%2C011%20interviews%20with%20people%20from%20135%20settlements%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20came%20out%20as%20Zelenskyy%20fired%20all%20the%20heads%20of%20Ukraine's%20regional%20military%20committees.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20all%20Ukrainians%20%E2%80%94%2089%25%20%E2%80%94%20in%20a%20newly%20released%20survey%20said%20corruption%20was%20the%20country's%20most%20serious%20problem%2C%20after%20the%20war%20against%20Russia.%20The%20poll%20came%20out%20as%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20launched%20an%20investigation%20into%20bribery%20related%20to%20military%20recruitment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20survey%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kiis.com.ua%2F%3Flang%3Deng%26cat%3Dreports%26id%3D1269%26page%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKyiv%20International%20Institute%20of%20Sociology%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20cooperation%20with%20the%20US%20Agency%20for%20International%20Development%20project%20%26quot%3BSupport%20of%20Leader%20Organizations%20in%20Combating%20Corruption%20in%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BSecond%20only%20to%20the%20war%2C%20corruption%20is%20perceived%20as%20the%20most%20serious%20problem%20in%20Ukraine%20by%2089%25%20of%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDespite%20a%20notable%20improvement%20in%20the%20public%20perception%20of%20corruption%20pre